caption.title: Clinical symptoms.
caption.p: Legend: The percentages for fever, pharyngalgia, expectoration, cough, weakness, headache, chills, and diarrhea were 100%, 67% (95% CI: 62% to 72%), 61% (95% CI: 55% to 66%), 59% (95% CI: 54% to 64%), 54% (95% CI: 49% to 59%), 48% (95% CI: 42% to 53%), 48% (95% CI: 42% to 53%), and 34% (95% CI: 30% to 40%), respectively.
